LINE.Text: You found your dream home and you are ready to buy. While it's exciting it's
also really scary. There's so much to do, so much paperwork to fill out and you
don't want to forget anything That's why the real estate attorneys at Scaffid
and Associates have created this infographic to help you understand the
process of buying a co-op. condo, or house from initial offer to closing!
In the case of cooperatives/condominiums, review board minutes, financials and offering plan.
In the case of cooperatives, submit a board package.
In the case of cooperatives, participate in a board interview.
Also in the case of cooperatives/cooperative, clearance from the managing agent.
